description: Fungal infections are among the most common and persistent types of infections in the world. They often go undiagnosed, and most people that have a fungal infection are completely unaware of it. If left untreated, fungal infections can lead to further health issues. Fungal infections are any condition you get from a fungus. They can be superficial and affect your skin, hair, nails, or mucous membranes (like mouth, throat, or vagina) or subcutaneous fungal infections which are under the surface of your skin. Also there are deep fungal infections that are found in places in your body other than your skin, like your lungs, blood, urinary tract, brain, or any other parts of your body. Deep fungal infections can be very serious.
